# Git commits

## Co-authored-by de agentes IA (OBLIGATORIO — siempre)

**Prohibido en todo commit** añadir `Co-authored-by` de Cursor, Copilot u otro agente, salvo petición **explícita** del usuario.

- No incluir esa línea en `git commit -m`, HEREDOC ni mensajes de amend/rebase.
- Si el IDE la inyecta, reescribe el mensaje sin ella antes de push.
- El hook `.githooks/prepare-commit-msg` la elimina al commitear; activar una vez: `npm run setup:githooks`.

Ejemplos prohibidos:

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Co-authored-by: GitHub Copilot <...>
Co-authored-by: <cualquier agente IA> <agent@...>
```

Los commits deben listar solo autor(es) humano(s) previstos.

## Conventional commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) when the repo already does: `type(scope): subject` (e.g. `fix(api): handle timeout`). Keep the subject imperative and under ~72 characters.

**Every commit must include a brief body** (1–3 sentences) after a blank line: what changed and why. The subject alone is not enough — even for small fixes and tests.

Example (HEREDOC with subject + body):

```
fix(api): handle upstream timeout

Retry once with backoff when the provider returns 504, so analysis
streams fail gracefully instead of hanging the client.
```

## When committing

- Follow the user's commit workflow (status, diff, HEREDOC for `-m` with subject **and** body).
- Do not amend or force-push unless the user explicitly requests it and safety rules allow it.
- Never run `git config` to change identity or hooks.
